# ghl-cli — optional environment variables. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) or just `export` them.
# Credentials are normally stored as named profiles via `ghl auth add`
# (in ~/.config/ghl/config.json, chmod 600). These env vars override that.
# NEVER commit a real .env or a real token.

# --- Auth (highest priority; overrides any saved profile) ---
# Create a Private Integration Token in GoHighLevel:
#   Settings -> Private Integrations -> Create new integration -> select scopes -> copy the token
#
# GHL_API_KEY=pit-xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx   # Private Integration Token (sent as Bearer)
# GHL_LOCATION_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx                   # default sub-account (location) ID
# GHL_PROFILE=work                                       # which saved profile to use by default

# Heads-up: if GHL_API_KEY is exported in your shell it wins over every saved profile,
# which makes `ghl auth use <name>` look like it does nothing. `ghl auth whoami` shows
# the profile, not the env override — unset GHL_API_KEY if a profile is being ignored.

# --- Misc ---
# XDG_CONFIG_HOME=/custom/path   # changes where config.json lives (default: ~/.config)
